<div id="about-the-community" class="section-spacer">
    <h2 class="sect-title">About Riverbend</h2>
    <div class="col-grid-2">
        <div>
            <p class="par-lg">A charming residential neighborhood in the south-east quadrant of Calgary, Riverbend is bounded by Deerfoot Trail on the west, 24 Street E on the east, Glenmore Trail on the north. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">The community has been developed within the Bow River floodplain.</p>
            <p class="par-lg">Established in 1982, the community in Riverbend is represented by the Ward 9 Councilor in the Calgary City council. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">A highly vibrant community, the Riverbend real estate enjoys a prime location in the heart of the city and offers a lot in terms of recreation for its residents. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">Homes for sale in Riverbend average some along the lines of mid 500s.</p>
        </div>
